Reasoning: The paper deals with decidability of bisimilarity for pushdown automata and first-order grammars, which are topics related to logic (cs.LO) and formal languages (cs.FL). The use of deterministic epsilon-steps and the comparison to the work of Senizergues suggest a connection to parsing and language theory (cs.PL). The regularity problem and the extension to nondeterministic PDA indicate a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and automata theory (cs.LT).
